    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I had hoped my good friend<lb/> to have seen you ere you left, but
                as I presume<lb/> your engagements have prevented I beg you to<lb/> hand this letter
                to <persName>Mrs. Hart</persName> with the deep assur-<lb/>ance of the friendship of
                one long tried who will<lb/> ever be interested in your well being. May the<lb/> God
                of <placeName>Israel</placeName> grant you success &amp; that you<lb/> may be able
                to dispose your enemies like chaff<lb/> before the wind; leaving that marble
                image<lb/> warms into life, not at the toil of the chisel but the<lb/> worship of
                the sculptor &amp; I do trust that your toil<lb/> will be repaid by a full
                appreciation of you by your<lb/> friends &amp; that your enemies even, will
                admit<lb/> how much as followers of <placeName>Israel's</placeName> God they
                are<lb/> indebted to you — If however disappointment &amp;<lb/> mortification shall
                be the reward of your labor's<lb/> leave not I pray you the field of Literature
                for<lb/> some less aspiring vocation — We cannot afford<lb/> to part with such a
                champion; you have unf-<lb/>urled your banner to promote the Glory of<lb/> your
                people, even when the even<add>?</add> hand of<lb/> persecution assails you still
                let it flout trium<lb/>phantly to the glory of God! Remember my friend<lb/> we cease
                to live when we no longer have some<lb/>-thing to do or to bear- unexpected
                disappointm<lb/>ents crush the hopes &amp; <add>?</add> the plans of the most<lb/>
                prosperous! Where is the individual upon whom</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the cares of this world will not sometimes press<lb/> I hope that I shall soon hear
                from you &amp;<lb/> of your triumph over your persecutions.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">May the God of <placeName>Israel</placeName> long preserve<lb/> you
                to do his will is the sincere wish</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">of your friend. <persName role="author">R. C. Moise</persName></p>
        </body>
    </text>
